makefile - creates a new empty file

Description:
The 'makefile' command creates a new empty file with the specified name. If the parent directory does not exist, or if the file cannot be created, an error message is shown.

Usage:
makefile <file_name>

Examples:
makefile notes.txt
makefile # Error: Invalid name provided.
makefile /nonexistent/path/file.txt # Error: Parent directory '/nonexistent/path' does not exist.
